  "texts": [
    "Currently this is not the case, among others, due to a lack of readily available gender-neutral/inclusive data, posing additional challenges for these data-hungry models.",
    "Rule-based or hybrid approaches that leverage linguistic knowledge in order to automatically generate gender-neutral alternatives in a post-processing way could be further explored to address the data scarcity issue, especially given the rather systematic nature of gender agreement rules (Vanmassenhove et al., 2021).",
    "Social bias in MT, refers to the bias that arises due to societal stereotypes and norms surrounding gender roles, which are embedded in and (un)consciously transmitted via the language in the training data.",
    "Such biases may influence the system to generate translations that align with traditional gender stereotypes or assumptions.",
    "Even more so because of the use of word embeddings which are used to capture semantic relationships and associations between words based on patterns present in the data."
  ],
